Update","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/145/s124"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–145, § 124","children":[],"tail":", as added by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/266/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–266, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-04-01"},"text":"Apr. 1, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/97"},"text":"106 Stat. 97","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/102/266/s102"},"text":"“The program authorized by section 534 of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2346c"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 2346c","children":[],"tail":"] may continue from funds appropriated by this joint resolution for foreign operations, export financing, and related programs, notwithstanding the last sentence of section 534(e) of that Act: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That such programs may include the protection of participants in judicial cases, notwithstanding section 660 of that Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2420"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 2420","children":[],"tail":"]: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided further","children":[],"tail":", That, notwithstanding sections 534(c) and 660 of that Act, (1) up to $10,000,000 to provide support for a professional civilian police force for Panama, except that such assistance shall not include more than $5,000,000 for the procurement of equipment for law enforcement purposes, and shall not include lethal equipment, and (2) up to $16,000,000 for Bolivia, Colombia, and Peru.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id8f9372f8-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Exe